31',0,'revision','',0),
	(132,3,'2014-08-01 21:39:12','2014-08-01 21:39:12','<p style=\"color: #000000;\">See a volunteer opportunity you like? Get started by completing a <a style=\"color: #780005;\" title=\"Volunteer\" href=\"http://www.ronaldhouse-sf.org/how-you-can-help/volunteer/\">Volunteer Application</a>.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Contact our Volunteer Coordinator, Melinda Prieto, at 415-673-0891 or email <a style=\"color: #780005;\" title=\"melinda@ronaldhouse-sf.org\" href=\"mailto:melinda@ronaldhouse-sf.org\" target=\"_blank\">melinda@ronaldhouse-sf.org</a> for additional information.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"color: #227896;\"><strong>Community Living Spaces</strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Designers, Artists, and Nurturers, help us make our House feel more like a home. We need your input, advice, and upkeep. Use your creative side to help update community bulletin boards to keep families informed.   Create a calm haven by arranging and updating furniture, toys and books in the communal living areas throughout the House.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"color: #227896;\"><strong>Events Committee Members</strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Do you enjoy throwing fabulous events and securing support from the community?  Our House has an annual Gala and Golf Tournament.  If you are interested in helping us with our events, contact our <a style=\"color: #780005;\" href=\"mailto:laura@ronaldhouse-sf.org\">Development Department</a> - please place “New Event Committee Member” in the subject line.  We are also searching for reliable, day-of event volunteers!</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"color: #227896;\"><strong>Facility Committee</strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Handy men and women we need you to assist with the maintenance and repair of the facility.  Projects may include: light maintenance, HVAC system, plumbing, electrical systems, exterior and roof – based on licenses and experience of each committee member. The committee will work with the Business Manager to determine repairs requiring third party expertise and knowledge.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"color: #227896;\"><strong>Gardening Committee</strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Do you have a green thumb? Help care for outside flower beds, trees, sidewalks and patio areas by planning, planting and maintaining all things green and beautiful. Check that automatic sprinklers and watering devices are properly maintained and adjusted for seasonal needs.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"color: #227896;\"><strong>Guest Room Committee</strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Help create a comfortable and individualized experience for the families that stay at the House. Stock guest supply closets, insure that bedding meets current family needs, identify required repairs in each guest room, insure that lights and fixtures are in good order, and check A/V units are functioning properly. You will also be encouraged to submit recommendations for possible room upgrades.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"color: #227896;\"><strong>House Supplies Committee</strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">If you like to organize and be hands-on this committee is for you!  Keep basement area backstock organized.  During the holiday season, instruct volunteers on which decorations will be featured. Properly label and store decorations and supplies when not in use.  Stock the Coke machine on a weekly basis.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"color: #227896;\"><strong>Information Technology Committee</strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Techies needed!! Use your computer skills to maintain and update our three guest computers, wireless system and WUFOO referral system.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"color: #227896;\"><strong>Kitchen Committee</strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">The kitchen is a beloved gathering spot for many families.  Help maintain the heart of our home by consolidating leftovers, replenishing condiments, arranging food storage areas and implementing sanitary food storing practices. Ensure that volunteer meal providers have the necessary supplies to prepare dinner. Review waste disposal and recycling practices to improve our current procedures. We look forward to your suggestions on improvements to make the workspace more efficient for families.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"color: #227896;\"><strong>Playroom Committee</strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Would you enjoy creating a safe, friendly space for children to thrive? If so, we’d welcome you on our Playroom Committee.  Help arrange and sanitize our playroom and patio area.  Make sure children can access age appropriate toys, make recommendations for new toys, retire old toys and help remove possible choking hazards.</p>','Friends of the House','','trash','open','closed','','friends-of-the-house','','','2015-01-19 15:24:10','2015-01-19 23:24:10','',43,'http://ronaldhouse-sf.org.97.69-195-223.groveurl.com/?page_id=132',2,'page','',0),
	(133,3,'2014-08-01 21:39:12','2014-08-01 21:39:12','<p style=\"color: #000000;\">See a volunteer opportunity you like? Get started by completing a <a style=\"color: #780005;\" title=\"Volunteer\" href=\"http://www.ronaldhouse-sf.org/how-you-can-help/volunteer/\">Volunteer Application</a>.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Contact our Volunteer Coordinator, Melinda Prieto, at 415-673-0891 or email <a style=\"color: #780005;\" title=\"melinda@ronaldhouse-sf.org\" href=\"mailto:melinda@ronaldhouse-sf.org\" target=\"_blank\">melinda@ronaldhouse-sf.org</a> for additional information.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"color: #227896;\"><strong>Community Living Spaces</strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Designers, Artists, and Nurturers, help us make our House feel more like a home. We need your input, advice, and upkeep. Use your creative side to help update community bulletin boards to keep families informed.   Create a calm haven by arranging and updating furniture, toys and books in the communal living areas throughout the House.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"color: #227896;\"><strong>Events Committee Members</strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Do you enjoy throwing fabulous events and securing support from the community?  Our House has an annual Gala and Golf Tournament.  If you are interested in helping us with our events, contact our <a style=\"color: #780005;\" href=\"mailto:laura@ronaldhouse-sf.org\">Development Department</a> - please place “New Event Committee Member” in the subject line.  We are also searching for reliable, day-of event volunteers!<a style=\"color: #780005;\" href=\"http://www.ronaldhouse-sf.org/test/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/Family-Meal-Volunteer4.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-416\" title=\"Family Meal Volunteer4\" src=\"http://www.ronaldhouse-sf.org/test/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/Family-Meal-Volunteer4-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"color: #227896;\"><strong>Facility Committee</strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Handy men and women we need you to assist with the maintenance and repair of the facility.  Projects may include: light maintenance, HVAC system, plumbing, electrical systems, exterior and roof – based on licenses and experience of each committee member. The committee will work with the Business Manager to determine repairs requiring third party expertise and knowledge.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"color: #227896;\"><strong>Gardening Committee</strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Do you have a green thumb? Help care for outside flower beds, trees, sidewalks and patio areas by planning, planting and maintaining all things green and beautiful. Check that automatic sprinklers and watering devices are properly maintained and adjusted for seasonal needs.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"color: #227896;\"><strong>Guest Room Committee</strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Help create a comfortable and individualized experience for the families that stay at the House. Stock guest supply closets, insure that bedding meets current family needs, identify required repairs in each guest room, insure that lights and fixtures are in good order, and check A/V units are functioning properly. You will also be encouraged to submit recommendations for possible room upgrades.<a style=\"color: #780005;\" href=\"http://www.ronaldhouse-sf.org/test/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/Family-Meal-Volunteer2.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-414\" title=\"Family Meal Volunteer2\" src=\"http://www.ronaldhouse-sf.org/test/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/Family-Meal-Volunteer2-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"color: #227896;\"><strong>House Supplies Committee</strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">If you like to organize and be hands-on this committee is for you!  Keep basement area backstock organized.  During the holiday season, instruct volunteers on which decorations will be featured. Properly label and store decorations and supplies when not in use.  Stock the Coke machine on a weekly basis.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"color: #227896;\"><strong>Information Technology Committee</strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Techies needed!! Use your computer skills to maintain and update our three guest computers, wireless system and WUFOO referral system.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"color: #227896;\"><strong>Kitchen Committee</strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">The kitchen is a beloved gathering spot for many families.  Help maintain the heart of our home by consolidating leftovers, replenishing condiments, arranging food storage areas and implementing sanitary food storing practices. Ensure that volunteer meal providers have the necessary supplies to prepare dinner. Review waste disposal and recycling practices to improve our current procedures. We look forward to your suggestions on improvements to make the workspace more efficient for families.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"color: #227896;\"><strong>Playroom Committee</strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Would you enjoy creating a safe, friendly space for children to thrive? If so, we’d welcome you on our Playroom Committee.  Help arrange and sanitize our playroom and patio area.  Make sure children can access age appropriate toys, make recommendations for new toys, retire old toys and help remove possible choking hazards.</p>','Friends of the House','','inherit','open','open','','132-revision-v1','','','2014-08-01 21:39:12','2014-08-01 21:39:12','',132,'http://ronaldhouse-sf.org.97.69-195-223.groveurl.com/?p=133',0,'revision','',0),
	(134,3,'2014-08-01 21:40:39','2014-08-01 21:40:39','<p style=\"color: #000000;\">As a volunteer, you will truly be supporting parents and children in the hospital. Every Child’s Bedside Program volunteer is screened and receives specialized training.  Once their training is complete, volunteers visit families in eleven major units at the hospital.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Our program currently runs four times a week: Monday afternoon, Wednesday afternoon, Thursday afternoon and Saturday morning.  Volunteers work on the day that best fits their schedule. As a volunteer, you will distribute beverages and treats to parents who remain next to their child’s bedside at the hospital and engage in friendly conversation with families who want to talk.  You’ll find that many families look forward to your visit!</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Our goal is to provide you with full training that offers the knowledge, skills and policies you will need during your shift. This is a one year commitment. We understand that the training process is thorough and time-consuming; however the smiles and appreciation from the parents you help will make the initial process seem like a distant memory.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">All volunteer candidates must be 18 years or older and complete the following orientations prior to placement:</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"><b>Step 1:  Complete </b>a <a style=\"color: #780005;\" href=\"http://www.ronaldhouse-sf.org/how-you-can-help/volunteer/\">Volunteer Application</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Step 2:  <b>You will be contacted to arrange an interview.</b></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"><b>Step 3:</b> <b>  You will be invited to attend the Volunteer Services orientation at UCSF Medical Center to learn about hospital policies and procedures.</b> Part of their requirement includes fingerprinting and a medical clearance from Occupational Health services.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"><b>Step 4:</b> <b> You will be invited to complete the Child Life Services training at UCSF Medical Center.</b></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"><b>Step 5:  You will begin experiencing the joy of volunteering!</b></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"></p>','Child’s Bedside Volunteers','','publish','open','closed','','childs-bedside-volunteers','','','2014-11-22 00:58:26','2014-11-22 00:58:26','',43,'http://ronaldhouse-sf.org.97.69-195-223.groveurl.com/?page_id=134',3,'page','',0),
	(135,3,'2014-08-01 21:40:39','2014-08-01 21:40:39','<p style=\"color: #000000;\">As a volunteer, you will truly be supporting parents and children in the hospital. Every Child’s Bedside Program volunteer is screened and receives specialized training.  Once their training is complete, volunteers visit families in eleven major units at the hospital.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Our program currently runs four times a week: Monday afternoon, Wednesday afternoon, Thursday afternoon and Saturday morning.  Volunteers work on the day that best fits their schedule. As a volunteer, you will distribute beverages and treats to parents who remain next to their child’s bedside at the hospital and engage in friendly conversation with families who want to talk.  You’ll find that many families look forward to your visit!</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Our goal is to provide you with full training that offers the knowledge, skills and policies you will need during your shift. We understand that the training process is thorough and time-consuming; however the smiles and appreciation from the parents you help will make the initial process seem like a distant memory.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">All volunteer candidates must be 18 years or older and complete the following orientations prior to placement:</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"><b>Step 1:  Complete </b>a <a style=\"color: #780005;\" href=\"http://www.ronaldhouse-sf.org/how-you-can-help/volunteer/\">Volunteer Application</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Step 2:  <b>You will be contacted to arrange an interview.</b></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"><b>Step 3:</b> <b>  You will be invited to attend the Volunteer Services orientation at UCSF Medical Center to learn about hospital policies and procedures.</b> Part of their requirement includes fingerprinting and a medical clearance from Occupational Health services.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"><b>Step 4:</b> <b> You will be invited to complete the Child Life Services training at UCSF Medical Center.</b></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"><b>Step 5:  You will begin experiencing the joy of volunteering!</b></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">*One year commitment.</p>','Child’s Bedside Volunteers','','inherit','open','open','','134-revision-v1','','','2014-08-01 21:40:39','2014-08-01 21:40:39','',134,'http://ronaldhouse-sf.org.97.69-195-223.groveurl.com/?p=135',0,'revision','',0),
	(136,3,'2014-08-01 21:41:40','2014-08-01 21:41:40','<p style=\"color: #000000;\">There are countless ways to raise money and generate support for the Ronald McDonald House! Gather your friends, family and co-workers to plan a neighborhood bake sale, family garage sale, cocktail party, car wash, jeans day, or wish list drive. For special occasions, like birthdays and anniversaries, ask that your guests bring an item off the wishlist or collect donations in lieu of gifts. The options are endless and no event or amount of support is too small. Be optimistic – excitement is contagious!</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">A third-party event or fundraiser is one which an organization outside Ronald McDonald House of San Francisco (RMH-SF) organizes and executes, and of which all or a portion of the net income after expenses benefits RMH-SF. The third-party organization is responsible for the major components of the planning of the event, including sponsorships, insurance, expenses, publicity, etc. RMH-SF will assist as staff time permits and is available for guidance, but the majority of planning and execution is the responsibility of the organization hosting the event.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Each potential event will be evaluated individually by the RMH-SF development department before it is approved.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"color: #227896;\">Third-Party Organization Responsibilities</h3>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">To get started, complete our <a style=\"color: #780005;\" href=\"http://www.ronaldhouse-sf.org/Download/External.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">external event form</a>, at least thirty (30) days prior to your event, and email it to <a style=\"color: #780005;\" href=\"mailto: laura@ronaldhouse-sf.org?subject= External Event Proposal \">laura@ronaldhouse-sf.org</a>  – please place “External Event Proposal” in the subject line of your email. You may also mail your application to:</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Ronald McDonald House of San Francisco\r\nAttn: Development Director\r\n1640 Scott Street\r\nSan Francisco, CA 94115</p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"color: #000000;\">\r\n	<li>A minimum of (60%) of the net income raised at the event should be designated to RMH-SF and/or other designated charities.</li>\r\n	<li>Provide copies of all publicity (i.e., television, radio advertisements, newspaper ads, flyers, website links, etc.) using the RMH-SF name or logo for approval prior to printing or distribution of materials. <em>All third-party organizations wishing to raise funds for RMH-SF, use the RMH-SF name and/or logo to promote the event and mention that proceeds will be donated to RMH-SF, must get approval.</em></li>\r\n	<li>Agree that all monies collected on behalf of RMH-SF will be presented to RMH-SF within 30 days after the event, unless otherwise cleared by an authorized officer of RMH-SF.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 style=\"color: #227896;\">We are happy to guide you along the way</h3>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">RMH-SF can assist in the following ways:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"color: #000000;\">\r\n	<li>Provide a letter of legitimacy for your organization on our letterhead stating that your third-party event is being conducted to raise funds for RMH-SF.</li>\r\n	<li>Offer advice regarding requests for sponsorships or donations (i.e. sample letter or advice on solicitation).</li>\r\n	<li>Provide event suggestions.</li>\r\n	<li>Other items or services as explicitly agreed upon.</li>\r\n	<li>Provide updated <a style=\"color: #780005;\" href=\"http://www.ronaldhouse-sf.org/Download/Wishlist.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Wish List</a> items.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">RMH-SF is honored to be the beneficiary of community events organized by individuals, local organizations, schools, and businesses. The funds raised help provide the necessary services for the families who call our Ronald McDonald House their home.  Thank you for your support!</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"><em>Notice: RMH-SF does not provide any financial assistance for production costs, insurance or other expenses for third-party events. The third-party organization will be responsible, financially and otherwise, for operating their event and in no manner will RMH-SF be liable for any claims or liabilities, no matter by whom made, in connection with the event.  </em><em>RMH-SF does not facilitate requests to the McDonald’s Corporation for sponsorship of third-party events. Approval of your event application does not constitute any relationship with the McDonald’s Corporation.</em></p>','Host a Fundraiser','','publish','closed','closed','','host-a-fundraiser','','','2014-11-24 14:42:21','2014-11-24 22:42:21','',35,'http://ronaldhouse-sf.org.97.69-195-223.groveurl.com/?page_id=136',4,'page','',0),
