	(158,3,'2014-08-01 22:41:36','2014-08-01 22:41:36','<h2 style=\"color: #227896;\"><strong>Referrals &amp; Admission</strong></h2>\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Requests for rooms at the Ronald McDonald House of San Francisco are made through the Department of Social Work at the hospital where the patient is receiving treatment. Due to the large number of referrals, we prioritize based on level of care, projected length of stay and distance from San Francisco. A request does not guarantee availability of rooms.</p>\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">The following requirements must be met to stay at the Ronald McDonald House of San Francisco.</p>\n\n<ul style=\"color: #000000;\">\n	<li>The patient must be 18 years or younger and receiving treatment in a San Francisco hospital.</li>\n	<li>The child’s permanent address must be at least 50 miles from San Francisco.</li>\n	<li>Adults staying in the House must have current, valid photo identification.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 style=\"color: #227896;\"><strong>Returning Families</strong><strong> </strong></h3>\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Returning families may call to verify availability and put their names on the waiting list.  Confirmation with the Department of Social Work at the hospital where the patient is receiving treatment will still be necessary.</p>\n\n<h3 style=\"color: #227896;\"><strong>Hours</strong></h3>\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">The House is accessible to families 24 hours a day, 365 days a year.</p>\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Registration Hours:</strong></p>\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Monday – Friday:  2 p.m. – 8 p.m. Saturday:  8 a.m. – 11 a.m. Sunday:  6 p.m. – 8 p.m.</p>\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Office Hours:</strong></p>\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Monday - Friday:  9 a.m. – 9 p.m. Saturday:  8 a.m. – noon Sunday:  5 p.m. – 9 p.m.</p>\n\n<h3 style=\"color: #227896;\"><strong>Check In</strong></h3>\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Your check in time must be confirmed with the Ronald 