ocal resources that may provide additional services other than those offered by RMH-SF.</em></p>\n\n<h3 style=\"color: #227896;\"><strong>Transportation</strong></h3>\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">The UCSF Medical Center operates <a style=\"color: #780005;\" href=\"http://www.campuslifeservices.ucsf.edu/transportation/shuttles/\" target=\"_blank\">free shuttle services</a> between the Ronald McDonald House and the UCSF Parnassus campus Monday-Friday, between 7 a.m. – 8 p.m. (excluding campus holidays). No eating, drinking or smoking is permitted in the shuttle vehicle. For more information, guests can call the shuttle hotline between 8 a.m. – 5 p.m. at 415.476.4646.</p>\n\n<ul style=\"color: #000000;\">\n	<li>The California Pacific Medical Center is a short MUNI bus ride away using the #2 or #4 bus lines.</li>\n	<li><a style=\"color: #780005;\" href=\"http://www.bart.gov/\" target=\"_blank\">Bay Area Rapid Transit</a> (BART)</li>\n	<li><a style=\"color: #780005;\" href=\"http://www.sfmta.com/cms/home/sfmta.php\" target=\"_blank\">Municipal Transportation Agency</a> (MUNI)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 style=\"color: #227896;\"><strong>Helpful Links</strong></h3>\n<ul style=\"color: #000000;\">\n	<li><a style=\"color: #780005;\" href=\"http://www.aap.org/\" target=\"_blank\">American Academy of Pediatrics</a></li>\n	<li><a style=\"color: #780005;\" href=\"http://www.cpmc.org/\" target=\"_blank\">California Pacific Medical Center</a></li>\n	<li><a style=\"color: #780005;\" href=\"http://www.carepages.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Care Pages</a> – Free Patient Blogs</li>\n	<li><a style=\"color: #780005;\" href=\"http://aacap.org/page.ww?name=Helping+Children+After+a+Disaster&amp;section=Facts+for+Families\" target=\"_blank\">Helping Children After a Disaster</a></li>\n	<li><a style=\"color: #780005;\" href=\"http://healthy.kaiserpermanente.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Kaiser Permanente</a></li>\n	<li><a style=\"color: #780005;\" href=\"http://www.sfdph.org/dph/comupg/oservices/medsvs/sfgh/\" target=\"_blank\">San Francisco General Hospital &amp; Trauma Center</a></li>\n	<li><a style=\"color: #780005;\" href=\"https://www.starbrightworld.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Starbright World</a> – Social network for teens with life-threatening medical conditions</li>\n	<li><a style=\"color: #780005;\" href=\"http://www.ucsfhealth.org/\" target=\"_blank\">UCSF Medical Center</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 style=\"color: #227896;\"><strong>Grief / Bereavement</strong></h3>\n<ul style=\"color: #000000;\">\n	<li><a style=\"color: #780005;\" href=\"http://www.compassionatefriends.org/home.aspx\" target=\"_blank\">Compassionate Friends</a></li>\n	<li><a style=\"color: #780005;\" href=\"http://www.dougy.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Dougy Center</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"><em>* Some of the listed resources were compiled by the Child Life Council.</em></p>','Guest Resources','','inherit','open','open','','156-autosave-v1','','','2014-08-01 22:41:36','2014-08-01 22:41:36','',156,'http://ronaldhouse-sf.org.97.69-195-223.groveurl.com/?p=158',0,'revision','',0),
