eing treated at their hospital.<a href=\"http://ronaldhouse-sf.org.97.69-195-223.groveurl.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/IMG_0027.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-546 size-medium\" src=\"http://ronaldhouse-sf.org.97.69-195-223.groveurl.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/IMG_0027-300x239.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_0027\" width=\"300\" height=\"239\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Murray enlisted the local McDonald’s advertising agency, who with the support of the McDonald’s Regional Manager , launched the St. Patrick’s Day Green Milkshake (now known as the Shamrock Shake) promotion. Funds raised went toward purchasing an old house located near the hospital.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">And thus, the first Ronald McDonald House came to be in Philadelphia in 1974 – a “home away from home” for families of ill children. The network of Houses quickly grew after that and today there are more than 300 Ronald McDonald Houses located in over 30 countries and regions world-wide. Each House is independently owned and operated. McDonald’s is only one of many generous donors, so community-wide support is the essential ingredient for each House.</p>','History','','inherit','open','open','','16-revision-v1','','','2015-01-14 14:35:35','2015-01-14 22:35:35','',16,'http://ronaldhouse-sf.org.97.69-195-223.groveurl.com/16-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
